Subject: Create a study plan
Description: Create a study plan that covers all the topics I want to understand and schedule time for review and practice problems.

Subject: Review matrix operations
Description: Review basic matrix operations such as addition, subtraction, multiplication, and transposition. Practice problems from the textbook and lecture notes.

Subject: Learn row reduction
Description: Learn how to use row reduction to solve systems of linear equations. Practice problems from the textbook and lecture notes.

Subject: Practice eigenvalues and eigenvectors
Description: Practice identifying eigenvalues and eigenvectors of matrices. Learn how to use them in matrix diagonalization. Practice problems from the textbook and lecture notes.

Subject: Study SVD
Description: Learn how to use singular value decomposition (SVD) to analyze data. Practice problems from the textbook and lecture notes.

Subject: Learn PCA
Description: Learn how to use principal component analysis (PCA) to reduce the dimensionality of data. Practice problems from the textbook and lecture notes.

Subject: Review all topics
Description: Review all the topics I have covered so far and practice problems from the textbook and lecture notes. Identify any areas that need more practice or clarification.

Subject: Take a practice exam
Description: Take a practice exam to assess my understanding of the material and identify any areas that need more work.

Subject: Review weak areas
Description: Review areas that I identified as needing more practice or clarification. Practice problems from the textbook and lecture notes.

Subject: Review everything again
Description: Review all the topics again and practice problems from the textbook and lecture notes. Try to focus on understanding the concepts rather than memorization.

Subject: Take a break
Description: Take a day off to rest and recharge.

Subject: Take the final exam
Description: Take the final exam and apply everything I have learned.
